  "texts": [
    "A TL approach with MobileNet V2 and Inception V3 base models is used to classify images across different geological tasks yielded high accuracies.",
    "This study is unusual in successfully applying these CNN models across a range of geological tasks.",
    "Because of the networks' reliance on curated and controlled datasets in this study, it is unclear how they will perform in real-world, uncurated environments, in which geological samples may exhibit greater variability and noise than those used in the training data.",
    "Ozer et al. (2023) introduce a novel hybrid approach that integrates a custom-built CNN with LSTM and BiLSTM networks for species-level classification of Globotruncana Foraminifera.",
    "The architecture features modified fully connected layers, where the final fully connected layer is replaced by LSTM or BiLSTM layers in the hybrid models, allowing the capture of both spatial and sequential features from the microfossil images."
